Trieste’s cultural complexity and its multi-ethnic environment. Slataper’s major literary achievement, My Karst and My City – a fictionalized, lyrical autobiography, translated here in its entirety – offers a unique example of an Italian modernist narrative, one that is influenced both by Slataper’s collaboration with the Florentine journal La Voce, and by the Germanic and Scandinavian literature that he absorbed while living in Trieste. My Karst and My City, together with the excerpts from his reflections on Ibsen and other critical essays included here, adds a new voice and a different dimension to our understanding of European modernism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Italian.2bisacsh  a1.  a20th.  aAustro-Hungarian empire.  aI.  aItalian nationalism.  aLa Voce.  aOne.  aScipio Slataper.  aTrieste.  aTriestine literature.  aTriestine.  aWWI.  aWorld War.  acentury.  airredentism.  amodernist Italian literature.  apolitics.  atwentieth.1 aBenson, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenson, Nicholas.1 aCoda, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoda, Elena, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP Pilot eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi